On this day eleven years ago Siphiwe “Shabba” Tshabalala brought Mzansi to its feet. The then Kaizer Chiefs star scored the famous opening goal of the 2010 FIFA World Cup. His thunderbolt against Mexico has been described as one of the most beautiful of opening goals for the tournament.  Shabba’s stunner has undoubtedly become the most famous goal in Mzansi football history. "It's Tshabalala ... goal, Bafana Bafana! Goal for South Africa, goal for all Africa!" Those were the exact words of renowned commentator Peter Drury when he described arguably the most beautiful Mzansi sporting moment. Where were you when this beautiful moment happened? 